02:33.387 --> 02:34.588
[baseball bat hits ball]

02:34.655 --> 02:36.424
[faint baseball game noises]

02:36.490 --> 02:38.726
Man: Wake up, Mort!

02:38.792 --> 02:42.530
- Young man, wake up!
 - Mort, get the ball!

02:42.596 --> 02:44.598
- [applause]
 - What are you doing? Get up!

02:44.665 --> 02:46.967
Right there next to you,
the ball!

02:47.034 --> 02:50.371
Get the ball! Mort!
 What is wrong with you?

02:50.438 --> 02:52.240
Announcer: That's another
 run for Pasadena!

02:52.306 --> 02:54.842
Get in here!
 Hit the bench, Mort!

02:54.908 --> 02:56.244
Way to go!

02:56.310 --> 02:57.478
I can't believe

02:57.545 --> 02:59.747
that faigele
 is my grandson.

02:59.813 --> 03:01.249
Man: How are we doing?

03:01.315 --> 03:02.250
You were fast asleep
 out there.

03:02.316 --> 03:03.351
Sit down!

03:03.417 --> 03:04.752
Hit another one.

03:04.818 --> 03:06.254
- Woman: Come on now.
 - Jerry.

03:06.320 --> 03:07.788
Jerry, get your mitt!
 You're in.

03:07.855 --> 03:11.191
Man: All right, Jerry, let's
 get some runs out there!

03:11.259 --> 03:14.428
All right now.
 Okay, okay!

03:14.495 --> 03:16.630
Look alive! Look alive!

03:16.697 --> 03:18.766
Woman: What's going on today?

03:26.407 --> 03:28.242
- Home.
 - All right, all right!

03:28.309 --> 03:30.878
Don't look at Bryna.
 Your sister can't help you.

03:30.944 --> 03:33.381
Hey, Jerry,
 you all right there?

03:35.716 --> 03:37.851
Try second. Second!

04:18.992 --> 04:21.329
[voices on TV]

04:34.041 --> 04:35.976
Hey, your mother is going
 to be back from work soon.

04:36.043 --> 04:37.978
You'd better have your
homework done, you know.

04:38.045 --> 04:39.480
[door closes]

04:39.547 --> 04:40.581
.. ...for a little
 respect around here.

04:40.648 --> 04:42.149
A nice warm meal--

04:42.215 --> 04:47.788
* Don't start
 collecting things *

04:47.855 --> 04:52.960
* Give me my rose
and my glove *

04:54.428 --> 04:57.398
* Sweetheart

04:57.465 --> 05:01.068
* They're suspecting things

05:01.134 --> 05:06.306
* People will say
we're in love *

05:08.509 --> 05:10.578
Wonderful, Shelly.
 Wonderful.

05:10.644 --> 05:13.146
Uh, brass section
 instruments, please.

05:13.213 --> 05:14.382
Hold on.

05:14.448 --> 05:16.650
You're very natural.

05:16.717 --> 05:18.919
There's still room for
 improvement, though.

05:18.986 --> 05:20.354
Why don't you come by
 after school?

05:20.421 --> 05:22.356
We'll work on it.

05:22.423 --> 05:23.857
Good.

05:29.229 --> 05:31.565
Okay, brass section.

05:31.632 --> 05:33.767
Somebody likes you.

05:33.834 --> 05:36.537
- Have we been practicing?
 - [bell rings]

05:46.113 --> 05:49.116
Okay, Shelly, see you
 at rehearsal for the play.

05:49.182 --> 05:50.951
It took you long enough.

05:51.018 --> 05:52.786
What were you doing?

05:52.853 --> 05:54.888
I never
 even heard you singing.

05:54.955 --> 05:56.957
Did you sing?

05:57.024 --> 05:59.527
If you did,
 what did you sing?

05:59.593 --> 06:01.294
Woman:
 We've tried everything.

06:01.361 --> 06:02.730
We've brought her
to the rabbi.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.331
We've seen a psychologist.

06:04.398 --> 06:05.966
I made cheese omelets,

06:06.033 --> 06:07.901
her favorite
 since I can remember.

06:07.968 --> 06:10.571
Nothing. She was fine,
 then all of a sudden she--

06:10.638 --> 06:12.473
She quit the play,
 and she stopped eating.

06:12.540 --> 06:14.942
Why won't you eat?

06:18.378 --> 06:20.681
[sigh] It's been
weeks at this.

06:20.748 --> 06:22.215
Shelly, I want
 to help you,

06:22.282 --> 06:24.151
so I'm going to ask you
 a series of questions,

06:24.217 --> 06:26.587
and you can just
answer yes or no.
How about that?

06:28.889 --> 06:31.291
Are you having trouble
falling asleep at night?

06:31.358 --> 06:33.093
Are there nightmares
 you want to tell me about?

06:36.864 --> 06:38.999
Have you ever taken reefer
 or any other drugs?

06:41.134 --> 06:43.170
Are you afraid you're going
 to be a disappointment

06:43.236 --> 06:44.972
or that you might
 let your family down?

06:46.840 --> 06:48.108
God damn it, Shelly,
 answer the doctor.

06:51.144 --> 06:54.181
Well, I'm going to give her
 a Miltown prescription.

06:54.247 --> 06:56.650
- Mother: What for?
 - Anxiety.

06:56.717 --> 06:58.351
Eventually, she's going
 to get hungry enough,

06:58.418 --> 06:59.820
and she'll eat.

06:59.887 --> 07:01.589
Do you know how lucky you are

07:01.655 --> 07:04.424
to have what you do after
what we've been through?

07:04.492 --> 07:06.259
We came here to get
 away from starving.

07:06.326 --> 07:08.161
And to choose not to eat?

07:08.228 --> 07:09.997
It's not the Holocaust.

07:11.298 --> 07:12.966
Do you want a barren womb?

07:15.402 --> 07:17.204
* [bells]

07:23.043 --> 07:25.746
Joni James:
 * Ask me how do I feel

07:25.813 --> 07:30.217
* Ask me now that we're
 cozy and clinging *

07:31.952 --> 07:34.221
* Well, sir, all I can say

07:34.287 --> 07:40.260
* Is if I were a bell,
 I'd be ringing *

07:40.327 --> 07:44.197
* From the moment
 we kissed tonight *

07:44.264 --> 07:47.768
* That's the way
 I've just got to behave *

07:47.835 --> 07:50.671
- * Boy, if I were a...
- Rose.

07:50.738 --> 07:52.673
You hear that?

07:52.740 --> 07:53.774
Yes, I do.

07:53.841 --> 07:55.142
So where are you going?

07:55.208 --> 07:56.376
Inside. I'm exhausted.
 I'm gonna lie down.

07:56.443 --> 07:57.611
You know what he's doing
down there.

07:57.678 --> 08:00.313
So what?
 Can't anyone be happy?

08:00.380 --> 08:01.849
It brings down
 God's judgment.

08:04.084 --> 08:05.619
Go talk some sense
 into that boy

08:05.686 --> 08:06.587
before it's too late.

08:09.289 --> 08:10.223
If you don't, I will.

08:13.393 --> 08:15.696
* And if I were a watch

08:15.763 --> 08:21.635
* I'd start
 popping my spring *

08:21.702 --> 08:23.604
* Or if I were a bell *

08:23.671 --> 08:28.241
* I'd go ding-dong
 ding-dong ding *

08:29.877 --> 08:31.912
* Ask me how do I feel

08:31.979 --> 08:36.950
* From this chemistry
 lesson I'm learning *

08:38.418 --> 08:40.253
* Well, sir, all I can say

08:40.320 --> 08:46.326
* Is if I were a bridge,
 I'd be burning *

08:46.393 --> 08:50.197
* Yes, I knew
 my morale would crack *

08:54.534 --> 08:57.170
Morty,
 we talked about this.

08:57.237 --> 08:58.238
Huh?

09:01.709 --> 09:03.110
Get dressed.

09:03.176 --> 09:04.444
You have to get upstairs

09:04.511 --> 09:06.346
before your zayde
 comes home.

09:06.413 --> 09:08.548
Listen to me. He can never
 ever know about this.

09:08.616 --> 09:10.851
Understand? Understand?

09:13.621 --> 09:14.988
You're
 a very pretty dancer.

09:19.593 --> 09:21.595
Your tante Gittel
 gave me this ring.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.966
Is Gittel Gershon's wife?

09:29.469 --> 09:30.570
Get dressed.

09:30.638 --> 09:31.939
Quickly.

09:46.486 --> 09:48.856
[chatter on TV]

09:53.761 --> 09:55.262
- Man: You ready?
 - Woman: Yes.

09:55.328 --> 09:57.164
Have you lived
 in the South? You have--

09:57.230 --> 09:59.266
- Yes, I have.
 - Well, I thought

09:59.332 --> 10:00.868
there was a little Southern
 dialect leaking through.

10:00.934 --> 10:02.602
I assume
 this is rigged, right?

10:05.205 --> 10:06.874
Without question.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.575
What do you want if you're
 Queen For a Day, Carol?

10:08.642 --> 10:11.378
.. Education aid and a collie
 dog for my older son.

10:11.444 --> 10:14.815
Yeah? Your older son?
 Well, now...

10:14.882 --> 10:16.717
- Where are you going?
 - Out.

10:16.784 --> 10:18.151
- Where?
- Where?

10:18.218 --> 10:19.319
Good night.

10:19.386 --> 10:20.320
Where?

10:21.855 --> 10:24.491
Sneaking in, sneaking out.

10:24.557 --> 10:25.625
Never home.

10:27.194 --> 10:29.362
Where is she going anyway?

10:29.429 --> 10:32.632
To Tom's or Joe's or Saul's.

10:32.700 --> 10:34.167
She's gone all the time.

10:34.234 --> 10:36.970
Expects us to fix
 her meshuggeneh kid.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.945
You like the meat loaf?
 I made it with...

10:45.012 --> 10:46.747
cornflakes.

10:46.814 --> 10:49.817
It's as filling as meat,
though, right?

10:49.883 --> 10:52.920
Mm-hmm. It's good.

10:52.986 --> 10:54.287
I never
 should have left you.

10:54.354 --> 10:56.023
Ha. You came back.

10:56.089 --> 10:57.324
You were the better woman.

10:57.390 --> 11:00.293
Yeah, yeah. She left you.

11:00.360 --> 11:02.262
Bryna.

11:02.329 --> 11:04.164
Yeah?

11:08.836 --> 11:10.971
Do you think I'm weird?

11:12.339 --> 11:13.340
No.

11:48.341 --> 11:49.509
Man on radio:
 There is no doubt--

11:49.576 --> 11:50.643
And I thought of everything.

11:50.710 --> 11:53.080
We got, um, candlesticks,

11:53.146 --> 11:55.448
matches,
 cartons of cigarettes.

11:55.515 --> 11:57.717
Oh, that's wonderful.
 I-- I worried about

11:57.785 --> 11:59.619
what I was going to do
 in the apocalypse.

11:59.686 --> 12:01.354
Uh-huh. Well,

12:01.421 --> 12:04.324
earthly pleasures will
 keep us sane, Yetta.

12:04.391 --> 12:05.893
Will we have chocolate?

12:05.959 --> 12:09.129
Chocolate? We got what,
 60 bars of chocolate.

12:09.196 --> 12:11.999
And we've got nine
 jars of pickles,

12:12.065 --> 12:14.201
uh, three dozen cans of tuna.

12:14.267 --> 12:15.602
Your zayde thought
 of everything.

12:15.668 --> 12:16.904
Don't you worry.

12:16.970 --> 12:18.505
It'll all be taken care of.

12:18.571 --> 12:21.608
If we each eat one bar
 of chocolate a week,

12:21.674 --> 12:24.111
then we'll have enough
 chocolate to last us 12 weeks.

12:24.177 --> 12:25.612
That's right. That's right.

12:25.678 --> 12:27.547
Look at this kid.
 he's a real Einstein.

12:27.614 --> 12:29.482
Oi, oi, oi, oi.

12:29.549 --> 12:31.819
12 weeks down there.
 The thought makes me cuckoo.

12:31.885 --> 12:33.520
Oh, but we'll all be together.

12:33.586 --> 12:35.722
And we're all
going to be safe.

12:35.789 --> 12:37.457
[sigh]

12:37.524 --> 12:38.959
What a guy.

12:42.896 --> 12:44.697
I'm still your father.

12:44.764 --> 12:45.866
- Bryna: Zayde.
 - Hmm?

12:45.933 --> 12:47.767
I want to try
 a math problem.

12:47.835 --> 12:50.603
- I want to do one.
 - Okay. Okay, okay, Bryna.

12:50.670 --> 12:53.040
How many cans of soup
 do we need for six months--

12:54.474 --> 12:57.010
...if we all share
 two cans a day?

12:57.077 --> 13:00.047
Um, how many months?

13:00.113 --> 13:01.882
Does Mom have
a bunker at work?

13:01.949 --> 13:03.083
I'm not sure.

13:03.150 --> 13:04.484
- Hey!
- If she doesn't,

13:04.551 --> 13:06.686
won't she get
 nucular exploded on?

13:06.753 --> 13:09.256
No. She gets under her desk.
 That's second best.

13:10.423 --> 13:12.392
Sure, sure, but if you--

13:12.459 --> 13:15.095
if you see a bunker,
 you run there.

13:15.162 --> 13:16.229
You don't want
 your eyeballs melting

13:16.296 --> 13:17.797
straight out of their sockets.

13:17.865 --> 13:19.666
Can eyeballs really melt?

13:19.732 --> 13:22.002
I don't want Mom's
 eyeballs to melt.

13:22.069 --> 13:23.036
That's not
going to happen.

13:23.103 --> 13:24.537
If anything, you know,

13:24.604 --> 13:26.706
she'll turn into
 a three-headed monster.

13:26.773 --> 13:28.909
What if Mom doesn't make it
 to the bunker in time?

13:28.976 --> 13:30.543
Sweetie, eventually,

13:30.610 --> 13:33.346
we will all be together
 in Olam HaBa'a.

13:33.413 --> 13:36.549
- Not to worry.
 - Heaven sounds like more fun.

13:36.616 --> 13:38.318
- The kids at school said--
 - Zayde: Yeah?

13:38.385 --> 13:39.819
...that the roads
 are paved with gold

13:39.887 --> 13:41.354
and you can walk
 on marshmallow clouds.

13:41.421 --> 13:43.056
- Hmm.
 - Oh, yeah? Convert.

13:43.123 --> 13:45.592
Go eat a Waldorf salad.
Go to goyische heaven.

13:45.658 --> 13:47.294
[Zayde laughs]

13:50.063 --> 13:52.099
* [easy listening]

14:00.573 --> 14:03.911
Sarah Vaughn:
 * Ooh-ooh

14:03.977 --> 14:06.179
* Make yourself comfortable

14:06.246 --> 14:09.849
* Ooh-ooh

14:09.917 --> 14:12.119
* Make yourself comfortable

14:12.185 --> 14:15.588
* Ooh-ooh

14:15.655 --> 14:20.093
* Make yourself
 comfortable, baby *

14:24.031 --> 14:29.903
* I've got some records here
 to put you in the mood *

14:29.970 --> 14:33.406
* The phone is off the hook,
 so no one can intrude *

14:33.473 --> 14:35.875
.. * Did you
 lock the door? Ooh *

14:35.943 --> 14:37.477
* I feel romantic *

14:37.544 --> 14:43.183
* And the record
 changes automatic, baby *

14:44.617 --> 14:46.353
* Sweetheart

14:46.419 --> 14:49.856
* We've hurried
 through our dinner *

14:49.923 --> 14:52.792
* Hurried through the dance

14:52.859 --> 14:56.329
[civil defense siren]

15:05.572 --> 15:06.673
Yetta!

15:08.275 --> 15:09.109
Yetta!

15:11.044 --> 15:12.479
Rose?

15:12.545 --> 15:13.880
Get up, get up.

15:13.947 --> 15:15.582
In the bunker. Let's go.

15:15.648 --> 15:17.017
It's just a drill.

15:17.084 --> 15:18.618
You don't know that.
 Get up. Come on.

15:18.685 --> 15:20.120
Okay, everybody.

15:20.187 --> 15:22.655
Yetta, Yetta, come on.
 In the bunker now.

15:22.722 --> 15:24.157
We don't need everything.

15:24.224 --> 15:25.358
Let's go. We're not
 fleeing Egypt.

15:25.425 --> 15:26.793
Where is Mort?

15:26.859 --> 15:28.161
Out you go, out you go.

15:28.228 --> 15:29.662
Move it, move it,
move it, move it.

15:29.729 --> 15:30.863
Where is he?

15:30.930 --> 15:32.332
- He's here?
- [siren blares]

15:32.399 --> 15:34.234
- What is he--
 - Stop it!

15:34.301 --> 15:35.535
All right, all right,
 all right, all right.

15:35.602 --> 15:37.804
Get in there.
 Turn around.

15:37.870 --> 15:39.539
Get in. Go. Keep going.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.308
Go. Keep going.

15:45.378 --> 15:47.780
- Shh.
 - Why are you wearing
 Mom's nightie?

15:47.847 --> 15:48.982
- Yetta: I'm going.
 - Zayde: Keep going.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.083
I'm going.

15:50.150 --> 15:51.784
I want you to hurry up.

15:51.851 --> 15:53.320
Go, go.
 You know what you're--

15:53.386 --> 15:55.655
You don't hear the siren?
Stand up.

15:55.722 --> 15:57.290
Zayde: Why are you
 blocking the ladder?

15:57.357 --> 15:59.059
Hurry up. You want--

15:59.126 --> 16:00.393
- Zayde: Keep going.
 - Oh, Mort.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.362
- Okay. Come on.
- Can't get his pants up.

16:02.429 --> 16:03.830
Why are you
 blocking the ladder?

16:03.896 --> 16:05.398
Nobody's blocking.

16:05.465 --> 16:06.699
Rose: Come on.
 Pull your pants up.

16:06.766 --> 16:08.168
Turn it. Turn it.

16:09.202 --> 16:11.538
- You need help?
- There we go.

16:16.343 --> 16:18.211
What the fuck is wrong
 with you, Mort?

16:18.278 --> 16:20.147
- Mom said it was okay.
 - Shh.

16:20.213 --> 16:22.315
What, you let your little
 faigele wear a dress?

16:22.382 --> 16:24.751
Stop yelling, okay?
 It's not her fault.

16:24.817 --> 16:26.619
Oh, for God's sake.
 I don't let him go
 to school like this.

16:26.686 --> 16:28.521
He's down here.
 He's playing. It's nothing.

16:28.588 --> 16:30.223
Oh, he's playing?
What kind-- What
is he playing at?

16:30.290 --> 16:33.060
What is this? He needs
 to see a doctor.

16:33.126 --> 16:35.462
And this-- Is this--
Hey, is this yours, too?

16:35.528 --> 16:39.199
What the hell
is all this, huh?

16:39.266 --> 16:40.133
- What is this?
 - Yetta: All right.

16:40.200 --> 16:41.301
This necklace.

16:41.368 --> 16:43.036
I-- I bought you
these pearls.

16:43.103 --> 16:45.405
I know. give it to me.
Enough with the yelling.

16:45.472 --> 16:47.274
You want to get thrown
 in the loony bin?

16:47.340 --> 16:50.210
All the Boymelgreen men,
they want to be women.

16:50.277 --> 16:52.345
This-- This family
 is cursed is what.

16:52.412 --> 16:54.947
It's not a curse
 on our family.
 This is our family.

16:55.014 --> 16:56.483
Family? Oh, family?

16:56.549 --> 16:58.651
You don't know anything
about being in a family.

16:58.718 --> 17:01.888
You're gone all night.
 You sleep all day.

17:01.954 --> 17:05.023
This is my house.
It's my rules.

17:05.092 --> 17:07.660
You don't pay for shit,
 my child.

17:07.727 --> 17:10.230
You do nothing,
 you get to say nothing.

17:10.297 --> 17:12.732
This-- This
 is all your fault.

17:12.799 --> 17:14.934
You want him to end up
 like Gershon?

17:15.001 --> 17:16.203
- Yetta: Haim!
 - Do you?

17:16.269 --> 17:17.204
- Haim!
 - Morty, come here.

17:17.270 --> 17:19.172
- Come to me. Look at me.
- Ow!

17:19.239 --> 17:20.673
Come here. It's okay.
 Sweetheart, come here.

17:20.740 --> 17:21.973
- Help me.
 - Leave him alone.

17:22.040 --> 17:23.376
- Leave the boy alone.
 - Mom!

17:23.443 --> 17:24.711
Come here.
You want to know

17:24.777 --> 17:26.146
what happened
 to your uncle Gershon?

17:26.213 --> 17:27.247
- Do you?
 - Haim! Stop that.

17:27.314 --> 17:29.182
You're being a schmuck!
 Stop that!

17:29.249 --> 17:30.750
He burned to death
 in the oven.

17:30.817 --> 17:32.485
- Oh, you--
 - You want to know why?

17:32.552 --> 17:34.854
Because your mother
 and your grandmother

17:34.921 --> 17:36.889
let him run around in a skirt!

17:36.956 --> 17:38.991
He only does it
when he's alone.

17:39.058 --> 17:41.294
It's just it makes him happy.
 It's nothing.

17:41.361 --> 17:42.562
[Mort crying]

17:42.629 --> 17:44.097
Is Gershon happy?

17:46.833 --> 17:49.336
You make him stop this,

17:49.402 --> 17:51.671
or you get
out of my house!

17:56.843 --> 17:59.246
It's the sirens, you know.
 They make him crazy.

18:00.413 --> 18:02.149
They make him crazy.

18:04.551 --> 18:05.718
Watch your head.

18:09.789 --> 18:11.791
You do what your zayde
 says, okay?

18:11.858 --> 18:14.961
[sniffling]
 I will. I promise.

18:15.027 --> 18:17.764
Don't listen to him.
 Please don't leave.

18:17.830 --> 18:19.666
Okay. You put your
 clothes on now, okay?

18:19.732 --> 18:21.168
Go get dressed.

19:02.209 --> 19:04.711
[footsteps]

19:08.114 --> 19:09.482
Mom?

19:24.297 --> 19:25.998
- Boy: Tommy, throw it!
 - Okay, let's go!

19:26.065 --> 19:28.235
[chatter]

19:30.069 --> 19:35.375
Red Rover, Red Rover,
 send Mary right over!

19:35.442 --> 19:37.710
[shouting]

19:39.446 --> 19:44.851
Red Rover, Red Rover,
 send Diane right over!

19:44.917 --> 19:45.918
[screaming]

19:47.720 --> 19:49.589
Stop!

19:49.656 --> 19:51.891
- Let's play it again.
 - Yeah.

19:51.958 --> 19:53.092
Yeah, let's play again.

19:53.159 --> 19:54.527
Come on, let's
 play it again. Yay!

19:54.594 --> 19:57.764
Hey, wait. I didn't get
my chance to cross over.

19:57.830 --> 19:59.499
The boys are over there.

19:59.566 --> 20:02.068
Red Rover is for girls only.

20:02.134 --> 20:03.903
[girls laugh]

20:06.639 --> 20:08.241
Bryna?

20:13.280 --> 20:15.282
You're a boy, Mort,

20:15.348 --> 20:18.050
no matter how many
 of Mom's dresses you wear.

20:18.117 --> 20:20.219
[giggling]

20:26.759 --> 20:28.528
Aah!

20:37.870 --> 20:39.872
[panting]

21:05.865 --> 21:09.001
[bell rings]

21:18.044 --> 21:19.512
[chatter]

21:21.848 --> 21:23.115
Ow!

21:23.182 --> 21:24.417
- What happened?
- Are you okay?

21:24.484 --> 21:26.953
- Bryna, are you okay?
 - [Bryan crying]

21:27.019 --> 21:28.054
Go get help!

