Oh, well, it's all
 wonderful, my dear.

22:35.354 --> 22:36.623
What's your favorite one?

22:38.090 --> 22:39.959
Oh, it's rare for me

22:40.026 --> 22:42.729
to be inspired
 by an individual piece,

22:42.795 --> 22:44.497
but I--

22:44.564 --> 22:47.366
I absolutely love the frames.

22:47.434 --> 22:49.201
[sputter] Ridiculous.

22:49.268 --> 22:50.703
Go, go.
 Receiveth your people.

22:50.770 --> 22:51.738
Should I say something?

22:51.804 --> 22:53.039
Uh, okay.

22:53.105 --> 22:56.142
Uh, I have a few words
 for everyone.

22:56.208 --> 22:58.645
Hi. Hi. Thank you
guys for coming.

22:58.711 --> 23:01.514
Um, I'm just
 gonna say a few things.

23:01.581 --> 23:04.116
Um, having an opening
 like this

23:04.183 --> 23:06.553
has always been
a dream of mine,

23:06.619 --> 23:08.320
and it's wonderful

23:08.387 --> 23:10.923
to have so many loved ones
 witness its birth.

23:10.990 --> 23:13.025
So thank you.

23:13.092 --> 23:15.762
Uh, I think my journey
 all started

23:15.828 --> 23:18.498
when I was a kid
 with crayons, right?

23:18.565 --> 23:21.367
I just remember sitting,
watching TV,

23:21.434 --> 23:22.869
and my mom gave me crayons

23:22.935 --> 23:24.437
because I could never
 focus on the TV,

23:24.504 --> 23:27.173
and I remember
I couldn't stop.

23:27.239 --> 23:30.076
And I would play with crayons.

23:30.142 --> 23:33.613
But the way my mom and my
 daddy would talk about it,

23:33.680 --> 23:36.148
it's like that was me
 kind of finding

23:36.215 --> 23:37.584
what I needed to do.

23:37.650 --> 23:39.552
And I got older.

23:39.619 --> 23:41.921
I remember doing
 ceramics and pottery,

23:41.988 --> 23:44.757
and it was a school thing,
 and it was good.

23:44.824 --> 23:46.693
- It was good, but it--
 - What are you doing?

23:46.759 --> 23:47.960
...but it wasn't it.

23:48.027 --> 23:49.529
Follow me.

23:51.397 --> 23:53.866
But wait for 180 seconds.

23:53.933 --> 23:58.137
...my voice. Acrylic
 is really my media now.

23:58.204 --> 24:01.373
Um, and it was
 a journey to get there.

24:01.440 --> 24:03.309
And when you look
at each piece...

24:03.375 --> 24:05.144
- 1...
- ...it's not just one...

24:05.211 --> 24:07.379
- 2, 3...
 - I think when you put
 a collection together,

24:07.446 --> 24:08.781
4, 5, 6...

24:08.848 --> 24:10.049
...it really is a meditation.

24:18.725 --> 24:20.092
[Shelly giggling]

24:20.159 --> 24:21.594
[applause]

24:23.429 --> 24:25.164
That ring should be
 on your finger.

24:25.231 --> 24:26.699
What? No. No, no, no.

24:26.766 --> 24:28.367
I want a pretty ring,
 Morton,

24:28.434 --> 24:30.036
not that facacteh thing.

24:30.102 --> 24:31.303
I don't--

24:31.370 --> 24:33.640
What are we gonna do?

24:33.706 --> 24:34.974
I don't know.

24:36.743 --> 24:38.778
Hmm. I just--

24:38.845 --> 24:40.246
I just need some time.

24:40.312 --> 24:44.016
I just need some time
to figure some stuff out.

24:44.083 --> 24:45.117
Okay.

24:46.185 --> 24:47.587
But until then--

24:51.223 --> 24:52.959
can you keep a secret?

24:55.995 --> 24:57.196
Can you?

